      <h2 id="le-wagon">Le Wagon</h2>
      <div class="content">
        <p>In June 2019 I joined the Le Wagon bootcamp in London, an intensive program which guides its students from a basic knowledge of programming to being a full-stack developer in 9 weeks. The program focuses on Ruby and Ruby on Rails, but HTML5, CSS3 with SCSS and SASS, JavaScript, SQL, ActiveRecord, scraping and parsing, JSON and RESTful API integration were also part of the curriculum.</p>
        <p>During my time at Le Wagon I decided to focus on the front-end as I realised it comes naturally to me. Contrary to the back-end the updates are visible, and I really enjoy finding the balance between elements as well as the right fonts and placements. In a future I would enjoy either working to a spec provided and match it to the pixel, or work with a designer to come up with concept for web applications.</p>
      </div>
